headline: S&P Global Launches StepForward: $10 Million Initiative Preparing Global Youth for AI-Enabled Futures
summary: S&P Global (NYSE: SPGI) today announced the launch of StepForward, a new philanthropic initiative aimed at equipping the next generation with the skills needed to succeed in an AI-enabled workforce.

headline: A Subpar Year for Software Stocks. 3 Charts Point to a Turnaround.
summary: Microsoft  the only $1 trillion software company, has gained just 5% over the past year.  As the second-largest holding in the iShares ETF behind  Palantir  Microsoft’s next move could dictate the overall flow of software stocks.  Bulls can remain vigilant above $464 where a double bottom base could take shape.

headline: S&P Global taps Booz Allen vet for CFO of planned mobility spin-off
summary: Kristine Martin Anderson, Booz Allen’s chief operating officer, will serve as the company’s interim CFO until a permanent replacement is found.
